"notes":{"slide-19":"1. Make the container directory:\rmkdir /vmdata/guest-images/vm-demo3\r\r2. Clone an existing VM:\rvirt-clone -o vm-demo2 -n vm-demo3 -f /vmdata/guest-images/vm-demo3/vm-demo3.qcow2 -d",
"slide-7":"Routed: guests are part of a subnet routed through a virtual switch - an external router needs to provide routing to the subnet being used",
"slide-14":"From within ‘hypervisor’ instance run ‘/vagrant/demo/mkvmdemo’",
"slide-4":"QEMU\nEmulated hardware (virtual network adapters, virtual disk adapters, etc.)",
"slide-9":"raw: file-based block device disk image\n\nqcow2: QEMU disk images (ver. 2) - supports sparseimages (file grows to set size as needed), COW (copy-on-write - make a clone based on a parent the only contains changes from the parent).\nhttp://www.linuxquestions.org/questions/linux-virtualization-and-cloud-90/kvm-disk-formats-difference-between-qcow2-and-raw-902995/\n\nLVM/Filesystem: uses existing mounted filesystem (block device) as the underlying disk",
"slide-15":"From within ‘hypervisor’ instance run ‘/vagrant/demo/mkvmdemo’",
"slide-21":"1. Save the instance memory to file:\rvirsh save vm-demo2 /vmdata/working/vm-demo2-backup --running\r\r2. Stops the VM\r\r3. Start the VM reboots it from POST\r\r4. Restore the last state of the instance memory from file:\rvirsh restore --running /vmdata/working/vm-demo2-backup --running\r\r5. VM instance now running with the restored state",
"slide-6":"NAT: guests must initiate communication - iptables on the hypervisor performs the NAT",
"slide-16":"From within ‘hypervisor’ instance run ‘/vagrant/demo/mkvmdemo’",
"slide-3":"KVM\nInterface to the kernel (memory, CPU, disk IO, etc.)",
"slide-8":"Bridging: each guest machine has a direct connection to the LAN through a virtual switch",
"slide-11":"/etc/vmbuilder/libvirt/libvirtxml.tmpl",
"slide-17":"1. Edit XML to allow '0.0.0.0' in the display device for VNC\r\r2. Open the firewall:\riptables -A INPUT -p udp --dport 5900:5999 -j ACCEPT\r\r3. Find VNC port of the instance:\rvirsh vncdisplay vm-demo2\r\r4. VNC into the host (w/ Chicken of the VNC)\r10.212.0.245:5900",
"slide-12":"Inject static files into a new instance (ie, public keys, scripts, etc.)\n\nFirstboot can act as a minimal shell-based provisioner (perhaps running a series of scripts copied in from the local system)\n\nDefine custom repositories to pull packages from to build instance\n\nInstall various packages as part of the instance",
"slide-5":"libvirt\nAPI to manage KVM, QEMU & virtualized machines\n\nSee Python example: https://github-enterprise.colo.lair/benk/kvm-tools/blob/master/vm-resources.py",
"slide-13":"https://github-enterprise.colo.lair/benk/infrastructure_services/tree/kvm-demo"}
